'''Gjernes''' is a [[contemporary art|contemporary]] style of [[fine art]]; [[sculpture|sculptural]] and decorative. It is a spreading popular style of art, especially in [[Scandinavia]], because the [[Norway|Norwegian Government's]] wedding gift to [[Princess Märtha Louise of Norway]] and her husband [[Ari Behn]] was two pieces of [[furniture]] work by [[Liv Mildrid Gjernes]].

A vast number of sculptural decoration assignments, for private and public institutions, have been accomplished in this style.{{citation needed|date=April 2015}}

