{{Italic title}}
[[File:Sueleymanname_nahcevan.jpg|thumb|right|Suleiman marching with his army in [[Nakhchivan Autonomous Republic|Nakhichevan]], summer 1554, during the [[Ottoman-Safavid War (1532-1555)|Ottoman-Safavid War of 1532-1555]]. One of the scenes of the ''Süleymannâme''.]]
The '''''Süleymannâme''''' (lit. "Book of Suleiman") is an illustration of [[Suleiman the Magnificent]]'s life and achievements. In 65 scenes the miniature paintings are decorated with gold, depicting battles, receptions, hunts and sieges. Written by [[Fethullah Arifi Çelebi]] in [[Persian language|Persian]] verse,{{sfn|Smith|2015|page=164}} and illustrated by five unnamed artists, the ''Süleymannâme'' was the fifth volume of the first illustrated history of the [[Ottoman dynasty]].{{sfn|Smith|2015|page=164}} It was written in the manner of the [[Iran]]ian ''[[Shahnameh]]'' epic.{{sfn|Grabar|1989|page=1}} The original version of the ''Süleymannâme'' lies in the [[Topkapi Palace Museum]] in [[Istanbul]].

