{{Infobox Artwork | image_file=TheBasketofBread.jpg | backcolor=#FBF5DF | painting_alignment=right | image_size=300px | title=The Basket of Bread | artist=[[Salvador Dalí]] | year=1926 | medium=[[oil painting|Oil on canvas]] | height_metric=31.75 | width_metric=31.75 | height_imperial=12.5 | width_imperial= 12.5 | metric_unit=cm | imperial_unit=in | city=[[St. Petersburg, Florida]] | museum=[[Salvador Dalí Museum]] }}
'''''The Basket of Bread''''' is a [[painting]] by [[Spain|Spanish]] [[Surrealism|surrealist]] [[Salvador Dalí]]. The painting depicts four pieces of bread with butter on them sitting in a basket. One is separated from the others and is half-bitten. The basket sits on a white cloth. The painting resides at the [[Salvador Dalí Museum]], [[St. Petersburg, Florida]].
The painting was completed in 1926 when Dalí was twenty-two years old, shortly after he had finished his formal art class in Madrid where he was studying the Dutch Masters.<ref>[http://www.daliweb.tampa.fl.us/25.htm The Basket of Bread at Daliweb.tampa.fl.us]</ref> It is among the earliest of several paintings of bread by Dalí; a later example is ''[[Basket of Bread]]'' (1945).
